The paper proposes two deep neural network architectures for classification of electrocardiogram (ECG) recordings, which involves both image processing (to extract features from the ECG signals) and temporal modeling (to capture the temporal dependencies in the ECG signals). Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers papers on various aspects of machine learning, including deep learning, which is the main focus of this paper. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category covers papers on image and video processing, which is relevant to the image processing aspect of the ECG classification task. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category covers papers on neural networks and related algorithms, which are the main building blocks of the proposed architectures. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers papers on various aspects of AI, including machine learning and neural networks, which are relevant to this paper. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): This sub-category covers papers on the interaction between humans and computers, which is indirectly relevant to the ECG classification task, as it involves the interpretation of ECG signals by human experts.
